# Spell Combinations

Individual spells solve immediate problems. Fireball eliminates clustered enemies. Shield prevents incoming damage. Heal restores wounded allies. But spellcasters who think only in single-spell terms miss the deeper tactical layer—spell combinations that synergize to create effects greater than their parts.

Spell combinations aren't just "cast multiple spells." They're deliberate sequences that manage Momentum economy while amplifying effectiveness. The wizard who casts two Sparks before Fireball generates Momentum while softening targets. The cleric who layers Mage Armor, Shield, and Blur creates defenses that cost zero net Momentum. These patterns separate competent spellcasters from masters.

