## Advanced Combination Tactics

### Turn Efficiency

Spells with different casting times enable complex sequences:

**Bonus Action Spells:** Cast alongside normal actions for double spell turns
**Reaction Spells:** Trigger off enemy actions (Counterspell, Shield)
**Concentration Spells:** Maintain ongoing effects while casting other spells

A wizard maintaining Haste (concentration) can still cast Fireball on their turn. The cleric concentrating on Bless still throws cantrip attacks. Concentration spells provide persistent benefits without preventing other casting.

### Attribute Flexibility

The same spell cast with different attributes creates different combinations:

**Mind-based Damage + Awareness-based Utility:** Fireball with Mind for maximum damage, Detect Magic with Awareness for perfect information
**Will-based Buffs + Presence-based Debuffs:** Shield with Will for absolute protection, Charm with Presence for social dominance

Mix attributes within combinations to leverage your strengths across different spell functions.

### Multiclass Synergies

Characters with multiple spellcasting archetypes (Wizard/Cleric, Paladin/Ranger) access broader spell combinations:

**Wizard/Cleric:** Arcane damage + Divine healing creates self-sufficient caster
**Paladin/Wizard:** Martial melee + Magical buffs enhances both capabilities
**Ranger/Cleric:** Nature spells + Healing supports wilderness adventures

These combinations require careful build planning but provide versatility single-class casters cannot match.

